$\frac{9}{2}$ means $9$ divided by $2$. We can do this by long division.
$$
\begin{array}{c|cc}
\multicolumn{1}{r}{4.5} & 9 \\
\cline{1-3}
2 & 9 \\
\multicolumn{1}{r}{8} \\
\cline{1-2}
\multicolumn{1}{r}{1} \\
\end{array}
$$
Therefore, $\frac{9}{2}$ expressed as a decimal is $\boxed{4.5}$. ки
